// Figure 4.3: Basket → Discount gRPC Synchronous Call
// Low-latency discount lookup during cart operations

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Basket API [icon: shopping-cart, color: green]
Basket Handler [icon: zap, color: green]
DiscountGrpcService [icon: code, color: orange]
Discount gRPC Server [icon: tag, color: cyan]
PostgreSQL [icon: aws-rds, color: purple]

// ==================== gRPC CALL FLOW ====================
Basket API > Basket Handler : CreateShoppingCartCommand
Basket Handler > DiscountGrpcService : GetDiscount(productName)
DiscountGrpcService > Discount gRPC Server : GetDiscountRequest (gRPC)
Discount gRPC Server > PostgreSQL : SELECT FROM Coupon
PostgreSQL > Discount gRPC Server : Coupon data
Discount gRPC Server > DiscountGrpcService : CouponModel (amount)
DiscountGrpcService > Basket Handler : Apply discount to item
Basket Handler > Basket API : Cart with enriched prices

// ==================== KEY COMPONENTS ====================
// DiscountGrpcService.cs: gRPC client in Basket.Application
// DiscountProtoServiceClient: Auto-generated from .proto
// CouponModel: Contains ProductName, Description, Amount
